🔥 ASSIGNMENT 6 — DEPLOY WEB APPLICATION USING PAAS (RENDER)
COMPLETE FINAL STEP-BY-STEP PRACTICAL SHEET
This is the final clean execution flow for deploying a Flask web application on a PaaS cloud platform using Render.

🎯 AIM
To deploy a Flask web application on a PaaS (Platform as a Service) cloud platform.

🧠 REQUIREMENTS
✅ Python Installed ✅ Git Installed ✅ GitHub Account ✅ Render Account ✅ Internet Connection

🌐 COMPLETE FLOW
Create Flask App
↓
Create requirements.txt
↓
Create Procfile
↓
Test Application Locally
↓
Push Code to GitHub
↓
Connect GitHub to Render
↓
Deploy Application
↓
Access Live Website

✅ STEP 1 — CREATE PROJECT FOLDER
Open terminal.
Run:
mkdir flaskapp

✅ STEP 2 — ENTER PROJECT FOLDER
cd flaskapp

✅ STEP 3 — INSTALL FLASK
pip3 install flask

🎯 WHAT THIS DOES
Installs Flask web framework.

✅ STEP 4 — CREATE main.py
touch main.py

✅ STEP 5 — OPEN main.py
nano main.py

✅ STEP 6 — ADD FLASK CODE
Paste:
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def home():
    return "Hello from Cloud PaaS Deployment"

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=5000)

🎯 IMPORTANT
host='0.0.0.0'
allows internet access to app.

✅ STEP 7 — SAVE FILE
Press:
* CTRL + O
* Enter
* CTRL + X

✅ STEP 8 — CREATE requirements.txt
⚠️ IMPORTANT: Do NOT use:
pip freeze > requirements.txt
because it may include unwanted macOS packages.

✅ CREATE FILE MANUALLY
Run:
nano requirements.txt

ADD ONLY THIS
Flask

SAVE FILE
Again:
* CTRL + O
* Enter
* CTRL + X

🎯 WHAT IS requirements.txt?
Contains: ✅ Python dependencies needed for deployment.

✅ STEP 9 — CREATE Procfile
Run:
touch Procfile

✅ STEP 10 — OPEN Procfile
nano Procfile

✅ ADD THIS CONTENT
web: python3 main.py

🎯 WHAT IS Procfile?
Tells Render: ✅ how to start application.

✅ STEP 11 — SAVE FILE
Press:
* CTRL + O
* Enter
* CTRL + X

✅ STEP 12 — TEST APPLICATION LOCALLY
Run:
python3 main.py

🎉 EXPECTED OUTPUT
Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000

✅ STEP 13 — OPEN IN BROWSER
Visit:
http://127.0.0.1:5000

🎉 EXPECTED OUTPUT
Hello from Cloud PaaS Deployment

✅ STEP 14 — STOP SERVER
Press:
CTRL + C

✅ STEP 15 — CREATE GITHUB REPOSITORY
Open:
GitHub
Create new repository.
Example:
cloudPr

✅ STEP 16 — INITIALIZE GIT
Run:
git init

✅ STEP 17 — ADD FILES
git add .

✅ STEP 18 — COMMIT FILES
git commit -m "Initial commit"

✅ STEP 19 — CONNECT GITHUB REPOSITORY
Run:
git remote add origin YOUR_GITHUB_REPO_URL
Example:
git remote add origin https://github.com/SonamUgale/cloudPr.git

✅ STEP 20 — PUSH CODE TO GITHUB
Run:
git push -u origin master
OR:
git push -u origin main
(depending on branch)

⚠️ IMPORTANT
GitHub password authentication is removed.
Use: ✅ Personal Access Token (PAT)
instead of GitHub password.

🎉 CODE PUSHED SUCCESSFULLY

✅ STEP 21 — OPEN RENDER
Open:
Render
Login using GitHub account.

✅ STEP 22 — CREATE WEB SERVICE
Click:
New +
Choose:
Web Service

✅ STEP 23 — CONNECT GITHUB REPOSITORY
Select repository:
cloudPr
Click:
Connect

✅ STEP 24 — CONFIGURE DEPLOYMENT
Fill:
Field	Value
Name	cloudpractical
Runtime	Python 3
Build Command	pip install -r requirements.txt
Start Command	python3 main.py
SELECT PLAN
Choose:
Free Plan

✅ STEP 25 — DEPLOY APPLICATION
Click:
Deploy Web Service

🎯 WHAT HAPPENS?
Render: ✅ clones GitHub repository ✅ installs Flask ✅ starts Flask app ✅ hosts application online

⏳ WAIT
Deployment may take:
* 2–5 minutes

✅ STEP 26 — OPEN LIVE WEBSITE
Render generates URL like:
https://cloudpractical.onrender.com
Open it.

🎉 FINAL OUTPUT
Hello from Cloud PaaS Deployment

🎉 PRACTICAL COMPLETED
You successfully: ✅ created Flask app ✅ configured deployment files ✅ pushed code to GitHub ✅ connected Render ✅ deployed live application

